==English==
===Etymology===
Anglo-Norman ''vill'', from Old French [[vile]] ‘farm, country estate’ (French [[ville]] ‘town’), from Latin [[villa]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /vɪl/

===Noun===
'''vill'''
# the smallest administrative unit of land in feudal England, corresponding to the Anglo-Saxon [[tithing]] and the modern [[parish]]

